CANVA REPORT — INSTRUCTIONS
============================

How to create your Canva Vulnerability Assessment Report:

STEP 1 — Go to canva.com and sign in

STEP 2 — Click "Create a design" → choose "A4 Document"

STEP 3 — Use this colour palette (copy hex codes):
  Navy background:  #1B2A4A
  High risk red:    #C0392B
  Medium amber:     #D68910
  Low green:        #1E8449
  Light background: #F4F6F9
  Body text:        #4A4A4A

STEP 4 — Page layout (8 pages total):

  Page 1 — COVER
    Navy background, white title text
    "WEB APPLICATION SECURITY AUDIT REPORT"
    Target, analyst name, date, grade badge

  Page 2 — EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
    Score cards: 3 HIGH (red) | 3 MEDIUM (amber) | 4 LOW (green) | Grade D (navy)
    Summary paragraph

  Page 3 — SCOPE & METHODOLOGY
    Table with target, tools, method, in/out of scope

  Pages 4-5 — FINDINGS (5 per page)
    Each finding card: coloured header + 4 rows (issue / why / evidence / fix)

  Page 6 — TOOL OUTPUTS
    Code-style text boxes with curl, DevTools, Nmap outputs

  Page 7 — REMEDIATION ROADMAP
    Priority table with effort estimates

  Page 8 — CONCLUSION + ETHICS STATEMENT

STEP 5 — Export as PDF (File → Download → PDF Standard)

STEP 6 — Upload PDF to your GitHub repo under /report/

CANVA TEMPLATE SEARCH TERMS:
  Search "cybersecurity report" or "professional audit report"
  in Canva templates for a matching base design.

NOTE: The full PDF report is already generated at:
  Vulnerability_Assessment_Report_DVWA.pdf
